<h2>Overview</h2><p>In this article, we’re diving into the preparation and painting process for the Excessive Industries NBO bumpers, which are designed to elevate your Jeep's off-road performance while maintaining a sleek look. Proper prep work is pivotal to ensure longevity and durability, especially when tackling tough trails.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>We’ll walk you through the essential steps needed to prep these impressive bumpers, highlighting both the products used and the techniques that will lead to successful paint adhesion and a professional finish.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Unboxing and Inspection:</strong> Start by carefully removing the bumpers from their packaging. These bumpers are tightly secured for shipping, so take your time. Inspect for any flaws or damage before proceeding.</li><li><strong>Cleaning the Bumpers:</strong> Use soap and water to wash off any shipping residue. Ensuring the surface is clean will prevent contaminants from impacting the painting process.</li><li><strong>Rust Preparation:</strong> You’ll want to use a product like Port 15 Metal Prep. This step is crucial as it transforms any surface rust into a stable zinc phosphate coating. Apply generously, allowing it to sit for about 15 minutes for best results.</li><li><strong>Rinsing:</strong> After the treatment, thoroughly rinse the surface to remove any remaining chemicals. This will leave a cleaner, rust-inhibited surface.</li><li><strong>Drying:</strong> Allow the bumpers to dry completely before applying any paint. This enhances adhesion and prevents any moisture-related issues.</li><li><strong>Painting:</strong> While rattle cans are commonly used, using specialized frame paint provides better coverage in hard-to-reach areas. Apply multiple thin layers rather than a single thick coat for even coverage.</li><li><strong>Curing Time:</strong> Let the bumpers cure for as long as possible before installation. A week is often ideal, as it allows the paint to harden and bond with the metal.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Use gloves to avoid leaving oil from your hands on the prepared surfaces.</li><li>If possible, work in a well-ventilated area to prevent inhaling paint fumes.</li><li>Keep your tools and workspace organized to ensure a smooth process from start to finish.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>By following these steps, you ensure that your Excessive Industries NBO bumpers not only look great but also stand up to the rigors of off-road adventures. Taking the time to prep and paint effectively can make a significant difference in the performance and aesthetic appeal of your Jeep build.</p>

